I have created a remote control in Lovelace using picture elements. The button are from imagefu.com.
The button png files are located in /local/images_tvremote directory which on hass.io is located in the www directory located in the config directory.
Each button is linked to a script which executes the relevant command(s).
I will include a picture of the remote as soon as I know how to add it.

The Lovelace yaml file includes the following:

####################################################
### Entertainment remote control                 ###
####################################################
        
  - title: TV
    icon: mdi:television
    cards:
      - type: picture-elements
        image: /local/images_tvremote/background_white2.png
        elements:
# Remote for Apple TV zitkamer
          - type: image
            tap_action: call-service
            service: script.atv_cursor_up
            image: /local/images_tvremote/atv_cursor_up.png
            style:
              top: 4%
              margin-left: 179px                     
          - type: image
            tap_action: call-service
            service: script.atv_replay_30sec
            image: /local/images_tvremote/atv_replay_30sec.png
            style:
              top: 12%
              left: 46px                     
          - type: image
            tap_action: call-service
            service: script.atv_cursor_left
            image: /local/images_tvremote/atv_cursor_left.png
            style:
              top: 12%
              left: 100px
